{
  "detail_href": "/docs/api/ops/einsum_path/",
  "detail_json_href": "/api-data/ops/einsum_path.json",
  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Evaluates the lowest cost contraction order for an einsum expression by considering the creation of intermediate arrays."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Specifies the subscripts for summation."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "str",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Specifies the subscripts for summation."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "subscripts",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "These are the arrays for the operation."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "list of array_like",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "These are the arrays for the operation."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "*operands",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Choose the type of path. If a tuple is provided, the second argument is\nassumed to be the maximum intermediate size created. If only a single\nargument is provided the largest input or output array size is used\nas a maximum intermediate size."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  },
                  {
                    "items": [
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "if a list is given that starts with "
                              },
                              {
                                "external_url": "",
                                "href": "/docs/api/ops/einsum_path",
                                "kind": "link",
                                "target": "einsum_path",
                                "text": "einsum_path"
                              },
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": ", uses this as the\ncontraction path"
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "if False no optimization is taken"
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "if True defaults to the 'greedy' algorithm"
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "'optimal' An algorithm that combinatorially explores all possible\nways of contracting the listed tensors and chooses the least costly\npath. Scales exponentially with the number of terms in the\ncontraction."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "'greedy' An algorithm that chooses the best pair contraction\nat each step. Effectively, this algorithm searches the largest inner,\nHadamard, and then outer products at each step. Scales cubically with\nthe number of terms in the contraction. Equivalent to the 'optimal'\npath for most contractions."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ],
                    "ordered": false,
                    "type": "list"
                  },
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Default is 'greedy'."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "{bool, list, tuple, 'greedy', 'optimal'}",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Choose the type of path. If a tuple is provided, the second argument is\nassumed to be the maximum intermediate size created. If only a single\nargument is provided the largest input or output array size is used\nas a maximum intermediate size."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "optimize",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Parameters",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Parameters"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "A list representation of the einsum path."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "list of tuples",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "A list representation of the einsum path."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "path",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
